Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, the former National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, declared on Monday that women are the most trustworthy partners in politics. Their importance in Nigerian politics, according to the former Edo State Governor, cannot be overstated. Women are considered to be more committed and loyal to both the candidate and the party, as he pointed out. Also Read: Obiano’s Wife Declares Senatorial Ambition, Apologises To Soludo He stated this at the first Edo North APC women’s conference, which was held at Iyamho, Uzairue, Etsako West Local Government Area of the State and was organized by the party’s women’s wing. “I must say that women are the most reliable allies in politics and I am admitting that their roles cannot be underestimated in Nigerian politics. “I commended them for coming out from their shell to seek political relevance and hold political offices in our country,” he added.